				<name type="primary" sortindex="1" value="Battle Fear: Monster Dice" />
			
						                           
						               													<description>Battle Fear flips the dice game on its head. Roll miniature figures to determine actions like attacking, healing, powering up, and drawing a card. The luck of the dice and strategy of playing cards makes this game perfect for kids and adults. A game so portable you can Battle Fear anywhere at anytime. &amp;#10; Set-up:&amp;#10;1. Players choose two Monster Dice. Each Monster has a Combat Card and a set of Backup Cards.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;2. Place the power tracker on the left and the health tracker on the right of the Combat Card. Each Monster starts with a specific power and health level.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;3. Shuffle the two sets of Backup Cards together and place them face down.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;How to Play:&amp;#10;1. Both players roll their Monster Dice. Depending on how they land have actions that are described on the Combat Card.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;2. Head - Attack any enemy -2 health. &amp;#10;Feet - Heal self or ally +1 health.&amp;#10;Face - Power up self or ally +1 power.&amp;#10;Back - Draw a Backup Card.&amp;#10;Sides - No Action&amp;#10;&amp;#10;3. Backup cards can be played when a player has enough power to use on that action.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;4. Adjust the power and health for each Monster on the Combat Card. Repeat.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Victory is achieved when both enemy Monsters have fallen to 0 health.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
